13/07/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Minister of Public Order Georgios Voulgarakis arrived in Istanbul on Monday (12 July) seeking Turkish assistance in providing security for the Summer Olympics, now a month away.
He is holding talks with Turkish authorities, who will share their experiences in securing high-profile events, such as the recent NATO summit.Greece is working with NATO and several countries to ensure the complete safety of the Games.
(Anadolu Agency - 12/07/04)
